        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 4 at 6:36PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 636 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles west of Two Buttes Reservoir, or 21 miles northwest of
Springfield, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Two Buttes Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
